  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AER 2014 Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sin Tax: implementation sin tax law, application of proceeds to universal health care and livelihoods support to tobacco farmers  
Tax Incentives: progressive law that tightens criteria for granting incentives and ties up system to good industrial policy
Minerals Taxation: minerals taxation rates to global practice and increase revenue from minerals 
FOI: passage of long-awaited FOI Law
IP: industrial policy enacted that goes beyond horizontal and facilitation instruments, introduces carefully considered vertical and sectoral interventions, to increase productivity, recover quality and sustainable jobs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sin Tax: monitor implementation,IRR and public dissemination, pilot PhilHealth reforms, counter industry propaganda, consolidate advocates
Fiscal Incentives: collaborate with DOF on FI bill, strengthen CSO involvement, enhance relations with Congress, issue regular statements on bill; work with academics &amp; WB 
Mineral Taxation: Help BK craft bill &amp; identify champions, Issue analytical pieces in newspapers &amp; online media, Engage committee hearings, Facilitate dialogue with industry
FOI: lead work with FOI networks, Engage legislators, Promote active FOI practice
Industrial Policy:IP updates, response to media and government reports, Research-finalize IP framework paper; 5 supporting research; Building IP Coalition, Engage government, Forums on select strategic industries; project on Yolanda Rehabilitation and IP to test feasibility of integrating IP in rehabilitation 
Engagement in Asian Tax Justice network and the Open Government Program</narrative>
  </description>
